":"","submitter_user":"thang","user_is_author":false,"tags":["mobile"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/7kaqfg","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/7kaqfg/what_makes_good_smartphone_camera"},{"short_id":"fk5hpa","created_at":"2026-05-05T01:45:59.000-05:00","title":"Ace Template: go from `rails new` to deployed in under 5 minutes (self-hosted or PaaS)","url":"https://github.com/jeromedalbert/ace-template","score":1,"flags":0,"comment_count":0,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"jerome","user_is_author":true,"tags":["ruby"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/fk5hpa","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/fk5hpa/ace_template_go_from_rails_new_deployed"},{"short_id":"hmunw6","created_at":"2026-05-05T00:57:19.000-05:00","title":"Inexpressibility in Exp-Minus-Log","url":"https://arxiv.org/abs/2605.01636","score":2,"flags":0,"comment_count":1,"description":"\u003cp\u003eTL;DR - all numbers defined in EML are computable (mainly because exp and log are computable for computable complex inputs, and the primary input ('1') is ofc computable) - this isn't as obvious as first thought, and you need some machinery from computable analysis. Ultimately, you get the canonical example of Chaitin's \\Omega_U is inexpressible in EML (it's left-c.e. but not computable).\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eEML is also shown to be equivalent to the EL numbers due to Chow (1999). Additionally, the expressions for x*y, -x, and x^{-1} are optimal (there are no shorter EML expressions for those, by exhaustive search).\u003c/p\u003e\n","description_plain":"TL;DR - all numbers defined in EML are computable (mainly because exp and log are computable for computable complex inputs, and the primary input ('1') is ofc computable) - this isn't as obvious as first thought, and you need some machinery from computable analysis. Ultimately, you get the canonical example of Chaitin's \\Omega_U is inexpressible in EML (it's left-c.e. but not computable).\r\n\r\nEML is also shown to be equivalent to the EL numbers due to Chow (1999). Additionally, the expressions for x*y, -x, and x^{-1} are optimal (there are no shorter EML expressions for those, by exhaustive search).","submitter_user":"unprovable","user_is_author":true,"tags":["math"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/hmunw6","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/hmunw6/inexpressibility_exp_minus_log"},{"short_id":"ljgmb5","created_at":"2026-05-05T00:12:47.000-05:00","title":"Using the WebView module with C++ and Qt Widgets","url":"https://www.qt.io/blog/using-the-webview-module-with-c-and-qt-widgets","score":2,"flags":0,"comment_count":0,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"rcalixte","user_is_author":false,"tags":["api","c++"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/ljgmb5","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/ljgmb5/using_webview_module_with_c_qt_widgets"}]